## Step 1: Understand the problem and define the probability of a match.
The probability of getting a match on the $i$th roll is $\frac{1}{n}$ because there is one favorable outcome (rolling $i$) out of $n$ possible outcomes.

## Step 2: Calculate the probability of no match on a single roll.
