## Step 6
To find $P(X - Y \geq 15)$, we need to standardize $X - Y$ by converting it to a standard normal variable $Z$. So, $P(X - Y \geq 15) = P\left(\frac{(X - Y) - (-50)}{130} \geq \frac{15 - (-50)}{130}\right)$.

